##Confirmed cases or contacts on multinational cruise ships

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Hu Zhenqing, reporter, thepaper.cn

Recently, the United States and many other countries, including Greece, have seen cruise passengers who have been diagnosed with or come into contact with new crown pneumonia, there is some concern that this could turn out to be something like the diamond princess, which broke out earlier in Port of Yokohama, Japan, in a severe outbreak.

A cruise ship, the princess, is currently moored off the coast of San Francisco, California, the CNN reported on March 6, the ship's passengers and crew are being tested for new crown pneumonia. The kits were delivered to the ship by a California Air Force National Guard of the United States helicopter, and medical staff from the US Centers for Disease Control arrived on the princess to test passengers for new coronary pneumonia.

Twenty-one people aboard the Princess Royal have tested positive for the new coronavirus, US Vice President Michel Pens√©e said Friday.

Nearly 100 people, including passengers and crew, will be tested, the ship's operator, Carnival UK, said in a statement. As of Friday, 45 people had been tested, according to CNN. There are 2,422 passengers and 1,111 crew members from 54 countries.

The diamond Princess, which was the operator of the Carnival Group, is the latest vessel to be hit by a severe outbreak in Port of Yokohama.

According to an AFP report on the 5th, the first death of a new coronavirus infection was confirmed in California on the 4th local time, the deceased and another newly diagnosed patient with pneumonia contracted the disease last month while aboard the cruise ship "Princess Supreme" , the two tourists were diagnosed with the disease after boarding the Princess Royal Between San Francisco and Mexico between February 11 and 21 and disembarking from San Francisco with other passengers on their way home, one of them, a 71-year-old man from northern California, died Thursday. After his death, the high princess cancelled her scheduled voyage to Hawaii.

California Governor Newson has ordered the "Princess" to return to San Francisco in the early morning of the 5th, the AFP news agency said, until the authorities on board the quarantine of all personnel until the completion.

"The CDC, the California Department of Public Health, and the United States Coast Guard are working together to determine when it is safe to dock the princess and how to get the passengers home, " Newson said, "The passengers came from all over the US, half of them from California. "

Meanwhile, a long-disembarked passenger of the Greek ship "opera" , currently in Greek waters, was confirmed to have contracted the new coronavirus, an Austrian citizen, the Greek newspaper I Kathimerini reported Saturday, it stayed on the cruise ship for about two weeks before disembarking in Italy on 28 February and returning to Austria.

When the Austrian side on March 4 informed that the Austrian man infected with the new crown virus, "opera" cruise ship is docked in Athens Piraeus port, for safety reasons, the "opera" cruise ship asked all the passengers who landed in the port of Piraeus to return to the ship as soon as possible. However, the passengers have been informed that the new coronavirus infection has not been on board for many days.

"Kathimerini" reported that the "opera" cruise ship has reached its final destination in Corfu, Greece, on the 5th, the Greek health authorities have allowed all passengers and staff to disembark without taking additional measures, after ruling out the possibility of new coronavirus infections on the ship. Currently, the ship's 1,579 passengers and 723 staff have disembarked.

Separately, a German cruise ship, the Aida Aura, with 1,200 passengers on board, was quarantined in Haugesund Port, Norwegian Sea, Wednesday, according to Bloomberg. Earlier, two passengers on the ship had been tested for COVID-19 because they had come into contact with a person who had been infected with a new coronavirus a week earlier and were immediately taken to Hockland, while the other passengers remained on board.

Fortunately, both passengers tested negative, and a doctor sent by the city of Hyugesund to check on the ship stressed that no one on board showed signs of new pneumonia and that the ship would leave the port as soon as possible.
